---
globs: .py
alwaysApply: false
---
- Use fewer comments
- Follow PEP 8 style guidelines
- Use type hints where applicable
- Prefer SQLite for data persistence
- Call `setup_logging()` once at entry point; use centralized loggers per major component (e.g., `logging.getLogger("app.core")`, `logging.getLogger("app.workers")`) rather than per-module loggers
- Always add `from __future__ import annotations` at the top of each file (enables modern type hints like `list`, `dict`, `callable` without importing from `typing`)
- Use ruff for linting/formatting
